Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows significant renal dysfunction (markedly elevated creatinine in both serum and blood, proteinuria), hypoglycemia, and low HbA1c. Urinalysis reveals glucosuria, proteinuria, ketonuria, and abnormal urine appearance (cloudy, brown, low specific gravity), suggesting possible acute or chronic kidney injury with impaired glucose handling. No evidence of urinary tract infection. Immediate clinical evaluation and nephrology consultation are recommended.
